1. Ja *pijem* kafu svakog jutra. (I *drink* coffee every morning.)
2. Oni *piti* sokove u parku. (They *drink* juices in the park.)
3. Ti ćeš me *pitati* za savet. (You will *ask* me for advice.)
4. Oni *pitaju* učitelja o domaćem zadatku. (They *ask* the teacher about homework.)
5. Ona će *pitati* za cenu ovog kompjutera. (She will *inquire* about the price of this computer.)
6. Oni su *ispili* sve sokove iz frižidera. (They *drank up* all the juices from the fridge.)
7. Ja ću *opiti* ovu čašu vode. (I will *drink up* this glass of water.)
8. Oni su *napijeni* nakon večere. (They are *drunk* after dinner.)
9. Ona je *pijana* od previše alkohola. (She is *drunk* from too much alcohol.)
10. Mi moramo *ispijati* vodu da bismo ostali hidrirani. (We have to *drink* water to stay hydrated.)

Note: The word "pit" has several different meanings in Serbian, such as "to drink", "to ask", "to inquire", "to get drunk", etc. The examples above showcase some of these meanings in different forms (infinitive, present tense, past tense, etc.) and positions in sentences.